Suspected Boko Haram insurgents have released Halima Umar, a corps member in Gwoza, Borno state, five months after her abduction. In a statement on Thursday, the state government said Umar was freed through collaborative efforts involving security agencies and an undisclosed journalist. Abdulmalik Biu, general officer commanding (GOC) 7 division of the Nigerian army, and the state director of the Department of State Services (DSS) handed over the corps member to Kadafur, the deputy governor at the government house, Maiduguri, on Thursday. â€œA serving corps member, kidnapped in January 2019… ~